review_blob: Tap at Level 33, Singapore. Hazy orange colour with a white head. Aroma and flavour of wheat, fruit, banana and some bitterness.
Tap at Level 33, Singapore. Black with a beige head. Aroma and flavour of roasted malt, coffee, chocolate, caramel and notes of hops.
Tap at Level 33, Singapore. Pours pitch black. Slight aroma of liquorice, some malt. Flavour of malts too, sharp alcohol after taste. Low carbonation, not bad.
Tap at the Level 33, Singapore. Cloudy amber colour, dirty. Light citric nose. Sweet taste, notes of lemon.Nothing amazing, but a good IPA.
Tap at the Level 33, Singapore. Hazy golden colour with a white head. Aroma and flavour of malt, grass, hops and fruit.

How: Bottle/Glass
Where: World Beers, Tokyo.
Appearance: Pale golden colour with a white head.
Body: Medium body, low to medium carbonation.

How: Bottle.
Where: World Beers, Tokyo.
Appearance: Pale golden colour with a white head.
Aroma: Peach.
Body: Light body, low to medium carbonation.
Flavour: Peach, sweet, fruit.
33 cl. bottle at a restaurant in Tokyo. Clear golden colour with a white head. Aroma and flavour of malt, hops and floral notes. Not great, but was okay with a meal.
On tap at Hob Goblin in Tokyo. Grassy hoppy aroma, clear amber brown, small white head, grassy, caramel, low bitterness, moderate carbonation.

Hob Goblin in Tokyo. Cloudy light straw color with white head. Malty aroma with herbal hops. Sweet light malt flavor with a herbal citrusy flavor , slight yeastiness. Low to moderate hoppy bitterness in finish.
Served on tap at the Hob Goblin in Tokyo. Not a bad cider, but could not drink more than one of these.
500 ml can from a Singapore 7/11. Clear golden colored with a short white head. Sweet and slightly fruity aroma. Malty caramel flavours with a note of hops. Hoppy slightly bitter finish.
500ml can. Pours clear golden colour with a short white head. Aroma and flavour of malt, low to moderate bitterness, fruit and a little hops. Nothing special.
330 ml bottle in Singapore. Not to bad, taste was a little metallic but crisp and dry. Thin white head quickly disappeared. Grassy aroma.
500 ml can from a 7/11 in Singapore. Low on aroma and flavour. Watery, slightly metallic after taste. Definitely nothing special.
Bottle. Dark brown colour with an off-white head. Red tint. Aroma and flavour of bread, roasted malt and with hints of hops. Quite sweet, slightly bitter.
Bottle. Pours clean yellow with a thin white head. Hoppy aroma, quite weak. Taste is malty with a medium bitter finish.

Bottle. Aroma of malted wheat, and some citrus. Pours pale straw yellow with a thin white head. A hint of grassy hops on the palate. Medium bodied with high carbonation. Smooth and quite drinkable, though nothing special.
beer_name: Big Sky Montana Trout Slayer Ale

review_blob: Poured from a 375ml can, gold amber in colour, short white head quickly disappears, floral fruity aroma , low carbonation, slightly cloudy, taste is very dry, fruity flavours, metallic after taste, low bitterness. Not bad, relatively clean tasting beer with no long lasting bitterness. Mmmmmm, beeerrr.
Can. Pale weak tasting beer. Moderate carbonation. No head. Weak aroma. Not great.

650ml Bottle served chilled in an Indian restaurant (New Zealand)
Pours golden, with a short white head. Light flowery aroma and palate. Slightly grassy. A bit watery but enjoyable.
500 ml can. Pours a deep reddish brown with a small beige head. Aroma of roasted malts, caramel toffee, chocolate, raisin. Sweet taste with a bittersweet finish. Decent ale.
beer_name: Gordon Finest Scotch / Mc Douglas Scotch Ale

review_blob: 500 ml can. Pours pale copper amber, small white head. Caramel and hops in the aroma. Tastes as smells - a little bit caramel, some hops. A little sweetness.
500 ml can. Large head. Crisp hoppy flavour. Very smooth, not a bad beer but wasnt really to my liking.
330 ml Bottle. Light golden, not much head, low to moderate carbonation. Tangy taste with a slight grassy hop aroma. Has a small smoothness but is a fairly average lager. Still enjoyable.
A sweet and floral flavour. Low bitterness. Pours light amber with a short white head.
330 ml Bottle. Pours straw yellow, with small long lasting head. Floral and fruity citrus aroma - similar flavours - one of the most flavoursome lagers ive ever had - and very enjoyable.
500 ml bottle - pours a murky, pale amber medium body with a moderate white head. Hops in the aroma, flavours slightly malty with strong hops / bitterness, but well balanced - a great beer.
beer_name: Two Metre Tall Forester Pale Ale

review_blob: Pours a clear red with a fair and lasting head - medium bodied with a nice smooth palate. Caramel, malt, fruits and hops. A very enjoyable beer.
beer_name: Saltram of Barossa Pepperjack Hand Crafted Ale

review_blob: Bottle; pours clear gold/amber with a thin white head - medium carbonation and thin body - mild to moderate bitterness - a little on the watery side.

Pours a clear gold/amber with a moderate off-white head. Slightly citrus aroma, medium bodied, low to moderate carbonation, a pleasant drink, with nothing outstanding flavour wise but is just a nice overall beer.
Poured a dark orange red with some visible sediment, most of which settled quite fast. No strong aroma, flavours roast, coffee. An enjoyable ale.

Served on tap (need to re-rate once buy bottle) - pours with a thin white head, fruity aroma, moderate carbonation, light bitter aftertaste - not much to say about this fairly ordinary lager - not as nice as most other beers in the James Squire line up.

Served chilled in a glass at a local Indian Curry restaurant, not a terrible beer but fairly ordinary - the pale amber lager pours with a fast dissipating white head. Slightly malty aroma - Quite a clean tasting beer , with a sweet fruity aftertaste - but nothing spectacular.

Pours a light red/brown coulour with a large white foamy head. Good lacing. Aroma quite fruity, malt. Flavours similar, dry mouthfeel. Moderate carbonation with low to moderate bitterness - 500ml brown bottle.

Pours a clear yellow colour with a medium white head. Aromas of fruit and malt. Fruity flavour of malts and caramel. Sweet hoppy finish. - 500ml brown bottle. No reference to Heather Ales on the bottle - just says Williams Bros Brewing Co.
Pours a hazy amber colour with a reasonable white head. No strong aroma.  Flavours rather plain, a little caramel maybe. Good bitterness. Enjoyable, but nothing great. - 50cl clear bottle.
Pours clear amber with a medium sized off-white head. Flavour quite sweet. Mild bitter finish. A bit thin bodied - nothing special. - 500ml brown bottle.
A clear brown / dark amber beer with a large long lasting white head. Sweet fruity aroma. Strong fruity malt flavours with a nice bitter finish. Great beer. - 500mm brown bottle.
Pours a hazy golden colour with good carbonation. Aroma and Flavours of citrus and banana. Quite an enjoyable beer - 33cl brown bottle.
330ml brown bottle. Clear yellow in colour, with a medium sized white head. Aroma and flavours of malt, hops and fruit. Quite nice.
Pours a red colour with a medium off-white head. Aroma malty and slightly citrus. Flavours, malty, caramel and hops. Not a bad beer but nothing special.

Not a bad beer, 500 ml bottle. Pours a golden orange with a small white head that disappears quickly. Medium bodied with low carbonation. No strong aroma. Slight bitterness. Flavours quite malty. Light bitterness in the finish - a pretty good beer.
Pours a dark yellow, with a thin short lived head - aroma is strong floral. Sweet flavours, with a nice bitterness in the finish. Medium bodied. Low/moderate carbonation. - brown bottle 330ml.
Pours a cloudy amber colour with a good head, medium bodied, nice bitter finish. Enjoyable beer.- 330ml brown bottle.
330ml bottle. Pours a golden color with a medium sized long lasting head. Aroma a mixture of fruit and alcohol, flavours - hops taste, fruity, medium bodied. Good beer.
Pours a pale golden color with a soft white head. Floral and malty aroma. Malty flavour but not to sweet. Medium to full bodied with moderate carbonation. An enjoyable beer, 330 ml brown bottle.
Pale yellow, sweetish, thin bodied, watery, boring. Just not a good beer. 330ml green bottle.

Dark brown color with a thin frothy off-white head that diminishesrather quickly. Aroma of roasted malt, slightly spicy. Creamy mouthfeel. Sweet roasted malt flavours with a spicy lightly bitter finish. 355ml brown bottle.
Pours clear yellow in colour with a medium white head. Aroma - malty, and a bit of fruits . Malty fruit falvours. Thin bodied and a bit watery though. Nothing special. - 330ml brown bottle.
